File: As of Friday evening, the total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa is 20,125. JOHANNESBURG - South Africa's COVID-19 related fatalities have gone up by 28. This brings the total national coronavirus death toll to 397. As of Friday evening, the total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa is 20,125. The total number of recoveries to date is 10, 104. READ: COVID-19: Global cases top five million The Department of Health says a total of 543, 032 tests have been conducted with 17, 599 done in the last 24-hour cycle. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.